AUTHENTICATION
──────────────
Polymarket uses a two-layer auth system:

  Layer 1: API Keys (L1 credentials)
    Derived deterministically from your wallet's private key via EIP-712 signature.
    Never expire. Never regenerate unless wallet changes.
    Header format: POLY-API-KEY, POLY-SIGNATURE, POLY-TIMESTAMP, POLY-PASSPHRASE

  Layer 2: EIP-712 Order Signatures (per-order)
    Every order is individually signed with your wallet key.
    Signature is embedded in the order payload — no separate auth step.

Signature Types:
  0 = EOA wallet (MetaMask, hardware wallet)
  1 = Email/Magic wallet (delegated signing)
  2 = Browser wallet proxy (smart contract wallet)

Key derivation (do this ONCE and store the keys):
  POST /auth/api-key  { Body: EIP-712 signed message }
  OR use createOrDeriveApiKey() — always prefer this

