REST API ENDPOINTS — CLOB (clob.polymarket.com)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

HEALTH & STATUS
───────────────
GET  /                     → "OK" — basic health check
GET  /time                 → Server timestamp (sync your clock to this!)

MARKET DATA (no auth required)
───────────────────────────────
GET  /markets                         → List all markets
GET  /markets/{condition_id}          → Single market by condition ID
GET  /order-book/{token_id}           → Full order book snapshot
GET  /order-books                     → Multiple order books
     Query: token_id (comma-separated)
GET  /midpoint?token_id={id}          → Best-bid/ask midpoint
GET  /price?token_id={id}&side={BUY|SELL} → Current best price
GET  /spread?token_id={id}            → Current bid-ask spread
GET  /last-trade-price?token_id={id}  → Last traded price
GET  /prices-history?token_id={id}    → Historical price data
     Query: interval (1m/5m/1h/1d), fidelity

IMPORTANT — Order Book Response Structure:
{
  "market": "condition_id",
  "asset_id": "token_id",
  "bids": [{"price": "0.65", "size": "1500"}, ...],   // sorted desc
  "asks": [{"price": "0.66", "size": "800"}, ...],    // sorted asc
  "hash": "..."
}

ORDER MANAGEMENT (auth required)
──────────────────────────────────
POST   /order                    → Place a new order
DELETE /order/{order_id}         → Cancel single order
DELETE /orders                   → Cancel multiple orders (body: [order_id, ...])
DELETE /orders/market/{market_id} → Cancel all orders for a market ← USE THIS FOR GAME-START WIPE
GET    /order/{order_id}         → Get order status
GET    /orders?market={id}       → Get open orders (optionally filtered by market)
GET    /trades                   → Get trade history
GET    /trades?maker_address={addr} → Get trades by maker wallet ← USE TO TRACK RN1

POST /order Request Body:
{
  "order": {
    "salt":          "random_uint256_as_string",
    "maker":         "0xYOUR_ADDRESS",
    "signer":        "0xYOUR_SIGNING_KEY",
    "taker":         "0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000",
    "tokenId":       "token_id_uint256",
    "makerAmount":   "collateral_amount_in_usdc_6decimals",
    "takerAmount":   "shares_amount",
    "expiration":    "0",                           // 0 = GTC
    "nonce":         "0",
    "feeRateBps":    "0",
    "side":          0,                             // 0=BUY, 1=SELL
    "signatureType": 0,
    "signature":     "0xEIP712_SIGNATURE"
  },
  "owner": "0xYOUR_ADDRESS",
  "orderType": "GTC",                               // GTC | FOK | FAK | GTD
  "maker": true                                     // POST-ONLY FLAG ← CRITICAL
}

IMPORTANT: makerAmount vs takerAmount:
  BUY  order: makerAmount = USDC to spend, takerAmount = shares to receive
  SELL order: makerAmount = shares to sell, takerAmount = USDC to receive
  USDC amounts use 6 decimal precision (1.00 USDC = 1000000)
  Share amounts use integer representation

Order Types:
  GTC = Good-Til-Cancelled (stays in book until manually cancelled or filled)
  FOK = Fill-Or-Kill (fill completely at price or cancel immediately)
  FAK = Fill-And-Kill (fill available, cancel remainder) ← safer for thin markets
  GTD = Good-Til-Date (expires at unix timestamp)

