════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
WEBSOCKET — LIVE DATA (wss://ws-live-data.polymarket.com)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Connection Flow:
  1. Connect: wss://ws-live-data.polymarket.com
  2. Subscribe to channels by sending subscription messages
  3. Keep alive with ping frames every 30 seconds

Subscription Message Format:
{
  "auth": {
    "apiKey":    "YOUR_API_KEY",
    "secret":    "YOUR_API_SECRET",
    "passphrase":"YOUR_PASSPHRASE"
  },
  "type":    "subscribe",
  "channel": "live_activity",
  "markets": ["token_id_1", "token_id_2"]
}

Available Channels:
  live_activity  → All order book activity (new orders, fills, cancels)
  user           → Your own order updates (auth required)

Order Book Update Message (delta):
{
  "event_type": "book",
  "market":     "token_id",
  "asset_id":   "token_id",
  "buys":  [{"price": "0.65", "size": "1500"}],  // size=0 means level removed
  "sells": [{"price": "0.66", "size": "0"}],
  "timestamp": "1711900000000",
  "hash": "..."
}

Trade Execution Message:
{
  "event_type":   "last_trade_price",
  "market":       "token_id",
  "price":        "0.65",
  "size":         "500",
  "side":         "BUY",
  "timestamp":    "1711900000000"
}

Order Placed Message (THIS IS WHAT WE SNIFF FOR RN1):
{
  "event_type":  "order",
  "market":      "token_id",
  "order_id":    "uuid",
  "owner":       "0xWALLET_ADDRESS",   ← filter for RN1 here
  "side":        "BUY",
  "price":       "0.65",
  "size_matched":"0",
  "original_size":"50000",
  "type":        "LIMIT",
  "created_at":  "1711900000000"
}

CRITICAL: When we detect RN1's order, we have milliseconds to respond.
The decision pipeline must be:
  Parse message → verify owner == RN1 → extract (token_id, side, price, size)
  → calculate our size → build our EIP-712 order → sign → POST /order

Maximum acceptable latency for this pipeline: 5ms end-to-end.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
RATE LIMITS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
REST API:   ~100 requests/second (unverified — test experimentally)
WebSocket:  1 connection per market subscription recommended
Order submission: No hard published limit, but aggressive behavior
            will result in temporary IP bans. Keep to < 5 orders/second.

Best practices to avoid rate limiting:
  1. Cache order book state locally — never poll GET /order-book on hot path
  2. Use WebSocket for real-time data, REST only for order submission
  3. Implement exponential backoff on 429 responses
  4. Use a single persistent reqwest::Client (connection pooling)

