════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
IMPORTANT EDGE CASES & GOTCHAS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. TICK SIZES vary per market. Always fetch tick_size from GET /markets.
   Common values: 0.01, 0.001. Orders priced outside tick increments are rejected.

2. NEGATIVE RISK MARKETS (negRisk: true):
   These are multi-outcome markets (e.g., "Which team wins the tournament?")
   They use a different CTF contract address (NegRisk Exchange above).
   Handle separately — different order book mechanics.

3. PRE-GAME ORDER WIPE:
   The moment a game starts, ALL open orders for that market are cancelled by
   the exchange. Your bot must:
     a) Subscribe to game start events
     b) Cancel orders 5 seconds before expected game start as a safety buffer
     c) Flush local order cache immediately on receiving the wipe event

4. 3-SECOND IN-PLAY DELAY:
   During active game: marketable orders face a 3-second placement delay.
   Your bot submits the order → it enters a queue → either executes or
   gets cancelled by our failsafe if odds move.
   NON-marketable (Post-Only) orders may not face this delay — verify this
   experimentally before relying on it.

5. PRICE REPRESENTATION:
   Prices are $0.01 to $0.99 (binary outcomes).
   $0.65 = 65% implied probability = 1.538x payout if correct.
   Always treat prices as decimal strings from the API ("0.65"), not floats.
   Parse to u64 (multiply by 1000) to avoid floating point errors.

6. ORDER SCORING:
   GET /are-orders-scoring?ids=... tells you if your orders are eligible for
   maker rebates. Check this to confirm Post-Only orders are scoring.
